The main road from Nicaea to Ancyra passed through Iuliopolis. Ancyra was the meetingplace of three great roads- (1) from Sinope3 this road crossed that from Nicomedeia to Amasia at Gangra, · and then was continued to Ancyra ; (2) from Nicopolis in Little Armenia, pass· ing Sebastia, also a great meetingplace oi reads, and Tavia; (3) from Melitene in Cappadocia, the headquarters of a legion, xii Fulminata.
